http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/All-set-for-annual-feast-of-St.-Lawrence-shrine-in-Udupi/article14015818.ece

: The annual feast of St. Lawrence Shrine at Attur near Karkala in Udupi district, which attracts devotees from different parts of the State and the country, will be held from January 24 to 28.Rev. Fr. George Dâ€™Souza, rector of the shrine, told reporters here on Friday that all arrangements had been made for the smooth conduct of the festival. The feast used to be held for three days, but this year onwards, it will be held for five days because of the increase in the number of devotees.The festivities will begin on Sunday with the celebration of Confraternity Sunday (brotherhood and sisterhood Sunday). The holy mass will be offered at 7.30 a.m., followed by the Eucharistic procession of the parishioners. On the same day, two special masses will be offered for the intention of the tiny children at 11 a.m. and 3 p.m. On January 25, there will be two special masses for the sick and the elderly at 10 a.m. and 3.30 p.m. respectively. There will be totally 42 masses, which will be offered by the bishops of Bellary, Mangaluru, Varanasi and Belthangady. Most. Rev. Dr. Gerald Isaac Lobo, bishop of Udupi will camp at the venue on all days.For the safety of devotees, around 75 CCTV cameras have been installed, and 350 police personnel will be deployed. Movements of all devotees will be monitored. A unit of the District Armed Reserved Police too will be on standby.